1 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES - FLOOR VERSION
2 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
3 1st Session of the 60th Legislature (2025)
5 and
6 Prieto of the Senate
7
8
9 AS INTRODUCED
10 An Act relating to elections; declaring that an
identification issued by an educational institution
11 is not valid proof of identity to register to vote;
amending 26 O.S. 2021, Section 7-114, which relates
12 to proof of identity for voting; clarifying that an
identification issued by an educational institution
13 is not valid proof of identity to vote; providing for
codification; and providing an effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 4-109.5 of Title 26, unless
19 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 An identification card issued by a school, university, or other
21 educational institution does not constitute valid proof of identity
22 for purposes of registering to vote in the State of Oklahoma.
23 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 26 O.S. 2021, Section 7-114, is
24 amended to read as follows:
HB1007 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 Section 7-114. A. Each person appearing to vote shall announce
2 that person's name to the judge of the precinct and shall provide
3 proof of identity, whereupon the judge shall determine whether the
4 person's name is in the precinct registry. As used in this section,
5 "proof of identity" shall mean a document that satisfies all of the
6 following:
7 1. The document shows the name of the person to whom the
8 document was issued, and the name substantially conforms to the name
9 in the precinct registry;
10 2. The document shows a photograph of the person to whom the
11 document was issued;
12 3. The document includes an expiration date, which is after the
13 date of the election in which the person is appearing to vote. The
14 provisions of this paragraph shall not apply to:
15 a. an identification card that is valid indefinitely, or
16 b. an identification card issued by a branch of the armed
17 services of the United States to a person who is a
18 member of such branch or is retired therefrom; and
19 4. The document was issued by the United States, the State of
20 Oklahoma or the government of a federally recognized Indian tribe or
21 nation; and
22 5. An identification card issued by a school, university, or
23 other educational institution does not constitute valid proof of
24 identity.
HB1007 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 Provided, if the person presents a voter identification card
2 issued by the appropriate county election board, such card may serve
3 as proof of identity without meeting the requirements of paragraphs
4 2 and 3 of this subsection.
5 B. 1. If a person declines to or is unable to produce proof of
6 identity, the person may sign a statement under oath, in a form
7 approved by the Secretary of the State Election Board, swearing or
8 affirming that the person is the person identified on the precinct
9 registry, and shall be allowed to cast a provisional ballot in a
10 manner consistent with the provisions of Section 7-116.1 of this
11 title.
12 2. A provisional ballot cast by a voter who declines or is
13 unable to produce proof of identity shall only be considered
14 verified and approved for counting if:
15 a. the voter's name on the affidavit substantially
16 conforms to the voter's name in the voter registration
17 database, except as provided in paragraph 3 of this
18 subsection,
19 b. the voter's residence address on the affidavit
20 substantially conforms to the voter's residence
21 address in the voter registration database, except as
22 provided in paragraph 4 of this subsection,
23 c. the voter's date of birth matches the information in
24 the voter registration database,
HB1007 HFLR Page 3
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 d. the voter's Oklahoma driver license number or the last
2 four digits of the voter's Social Security number on
3 the affidavit matches the information in the voter
4 registration database. The provisions of this
5 subparagraph shall not apply if the voter was not
6 required to provide a driver license number or the
7 last four digits of the voter's Social Security number
8 at the time of registration, and
9 e. the provisional ballot meets the eligibility
10 requirements set forth in Section 7-116.1 of this
11 title.
12 3. A voter casting a provisional ballot as provided in this
13 section who has legally changed his or her name, but has not updated
14 the name on the voter registry, may note this fact on the affidavit
15 and submit a form prescribed by the Secretary of the State Election
16 Board to update his or her name. In such a case, and where the
17 requirements of Section 4-117 of this title are satisfied, the
18 provisional ballot shall be deemed to meet the requirements of
19 subparagraph a of paragraph 2 of this subsection.
20 4. A voter casting a provisional ballot as provided in this
21 section who has changed his or her address of residence, but has not
22 updated the address on the voter registry, may note this fact on the
23 affidavit and submit a form to update the address prescribed by the
24 Secretary of the State Election Board. In such a case, and where
HB1007 HFLR Page 4
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 the requirements of Section 4-117 of this title are satisfied, the
2 provisional ballot shall be deemed to meet the requirements of
3 subparagraph a of paragraph 2 of this subsection.
4 5. False swearing or affirming under oath shall be punishable
5 as a felony as provided in Section 16-103 of this title, and the
6 penalty shall be distinctly set forth on the face of the statement.
7 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
